Bring a #medium saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp}. Halve, peel
and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Halve the @green pepper{1}, remove and discard
the core. Chop into small chunks. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and
all), drain and rinse the @black beans{1%tin} in a #colander{}.

When the water is boiling, add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.
Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}, cover with a #lid{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a #large saucepan{} on medium-high
heat. Add the @British beef mince{120%g} to the pan, season with @salt{}
and @ground black pepper{}. Cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a
#wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Add the red onion, cook, stirring
occasionally until starting to soften, ~{2%minutes}. Add the pepper and cook,
stirring occasionally, for another ~{3%minutes}.

> Step 3 MOD: If you've added beef mince to your meal, heat a splash of oil in a large pan
> on medium-high heat as instructed. Before you cook the veg, add the beef mince to the pan,
> season with salt and pepper. Cook until browned. Add the onion and cook as stated. Continue
> with the recipe as instructed.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{1%tbsp} and @tomato puree{30%g}. Cook, stirring,
for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1%tbsp}, @finely chopped tomatoes
with onion and garlic{1%tin}, @BBQ sauce{32%g} and black beans. Add a pinch of
@?sugar{pinch} if you have some. Bring to the boil, stir to dissolve the stock
powder, lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the @soured cream{75%g} in a #small bowl{}. Grate in the @lime{1/2} zest,
mix well and season to taste with @salt and @ground black pepper{}. Chop the lime
into wedges.

Stir the @baby spinach{100%g} through the chilli, one handful at a time, until wilted,
~{2-3%minutes}. Season the chilli to taste with salt and pepper. Add a splash of
@?water{splash} to loosen if you like. Serve the rice in #bowls{} topped with the
chilli. Add a drizzle of the zesty soured cream and a sprinkle of coriander.
Finish with the lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!